'S e ''' Bogha Mòr''' neo '''Am Bogha Mòr''' <ref>[http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/vli/language/gaelic/pdfs/placenamesA-B.pdf  Iain Mac an Tailleir], "Placenames", duilleag 22, Pàrlamaid na h-Alba</ref> (Beurla: ''Bowmore'')
am [[prìomh-bhaile]] ann an [[Ìle]]. Tha e ainmeil airson an taigh-staile aige  agus an [[uisge-beatha]] ris an canar: ''Bowmore Single Malt''. 
 
Chaidh am baile a stèideachadh anns a’ bliadhna 1770. Ann an 2001 bha 862 duine a’ fuireach an seo.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Scotland's Census Results Online|title =Staitistearachd Bowmore Locality | url=http://www.scrol.gov.uk/scrol/browser/profile.jsp?profile=Population&mainArea=bowmore&mainLevel=Locality | date = 2001-04-29| accessdate =2008-08-31 }}</ref> 

